paragraphs.title: Display Top 5 Most Suspicious Fraud Policy Holder claims WHERE two or more previous claims submitted
paragraphs.text:
%sql
-- Top 5 most suspicious fraud policy holder claims
select * from
(select POLICYNUMBER, round(prob_fraud*100,2) percent_fraud,
      rank() over (order by prob_fraud desc) rnk from
(select POLICYNUMBER, prediction_probability(CLAIMSMODEL, '0' using *) prob_fraud
from CLAIMS
))
where rnk <= 5
order by percent_fraud desc;

paragraphs.title: Show Most Suspicious CLAIMS in Table in Descending Suspicion
paragraphs.text:
%sql
-- Sort the most suspicious fraud policy holder claims by liklihood to be anomalous.
-- Default is to show the top 1000 records.
select * from
(select POLICYNUMBER, AGEOFVEHICLE, AGEOFPOLICYHOLDER, WITNESSPRESENT, round(prob_fraud*100,2) percent_fraud,
      rank() over (order by prob_fraud desc) rnk from
(select POLICYNUMBER, AGEOFVEHICLE, AGEOFPOLICYHOLDER, WITNESSPRESENT, prediction_probability(CLAIMSMODEL, '0' using *) prob_fraud
from CLAIMS
))
order by percent_fraud desc;
